_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2744, \"end\": 2750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9374100470996596, \"rank\": 0.06676902289838449, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2805, \"end\": 2813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6445682992702308e-26, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jokic on his own could be enough to beat anyone, but Serbia is more than just Jokic.\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2911, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2880, \"end\": 2886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9374100470996596, \"rank\": 0.06676902289838449, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Atlanta Hawks wing Bogdan Bogdanovic and Charlotte Hornets guard Vasilije Micic will join him as will Micic's former Hornets teammate Aleksej Pokusevski.\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 3065, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2912, \"end\": 2925, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_Hawks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.439984703469858e-74, \"text\": \"Atlanta Hawks\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_Hawks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta_Hawks\"}, {\"begin\": 3054, \"end\": 3064, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksej_Poku\\u0161evski\", \"score\": 0.9850358329406838, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pokusevski\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksej_Poku\\u0161evski\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksej_Poku\\u0161evski\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An injury to Miami Heat forward Nikola Jovic has removed him from their Olympic squad but plenty of talent is ready to take his spot.\", \"from\": 3066, \"to\": 3199, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aleksa Avramovic, who played a great game against Gilgeous-Alexander at last summer's FIBA World Cup semifinals will be back this summer, joined by Memphis Grizzlies stash Vanja Marinkovic, former Grizzlie Marko Guduric, Brooklyn Nets stash Nikola Milutinov, former two-month NBA journeyman Filip Petrusev, and plenty of elite pros with a strong understanding of what it takes to win big international games.\", \"from\": 3201, \"to\": 3609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3201, \"end\": 3207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksa_\\u0110ura\\u0161evi\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.454999991887014, \"rank\": 0.8131868131871149, \"text\": \"Aleksa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksa_\\u0110ura\\u0161evi\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleksa_\\u0110ura\\u0161evi\\u0107\"}, {\"begin\": 3349, \"end\": 3366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Memphis_Grizzlies\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2093353545491115e-44, \"text\": \"Memphis Grizzlies\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Memphis_Grizzlies\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Memphis_Grizzlies\"}, {\"begin\": 3442, \"end\": 3458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Milutinov\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nikola Milutinov\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Milutinov\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nikola_Milutinov\"}, {\"begin\": 3477, \"end\": 3480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0288350946681754e-56, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 3492, \"end\": 3506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filip_Petru\\u0161ev\", \"score\": 0.9999999262890951, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Filip Petrusev\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filip_Petru\\u0161ev\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Filip_Petru\\u0161ev\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The big question for Serbia will be whether head coach Svetislav Pesic is prepared to feed the ball to Jokic as often as possible.\", \"from\": 3611, \"to\": 3741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3632, \"end\": 3638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9374100470996596, \"rank\": 0.06676902289838449, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3666, \"end\": 3681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Svetislav_Pe\\u0161i\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.9999999993333404, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Svetislav Pesic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Svetislav_Pe\\u0161i\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Svetislav_Pe\\u0161i\\u0107\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"International coaches like to distribute offense somewhat evenly.\", \"from\": 3742, \"to\": 3807, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Simply put, they are not used to coaching players who are good enough to take nearly 30 shots in a game.\", \"from\": 3808, \"to\": 3912, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A team effort might be best for Serbia in certain matchups, but if they are to take down Team USA their recipe for success will start with a big game from Jokic, and his teammates filling in as he draws more attention.\", \"from\": 3913, \"to\": 4131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3945, \"end\": 3951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9374100470996596, \"rank\": 0.06676902289838449, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4002, \"end\": 4010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6445682992702308e-26, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Serbia and Team USA have been drawn into Group C together and will face each other for their opening game on Sunday, July 28.\", \"from\": 4133, \"to\": 4258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4133, \"end\": 4139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9374100470996596, \"rank\": 0.06676902289838449, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4144, \"end\": 4152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6445682992702308e-26, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4174, \"end\": 4181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Euro_2012_Group_C\", \"score\": 0.9999990974333267, \"rank\": 9.025576189968099e-07, \"text\": \"Group C\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Euro_2012_Group_C\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Euro_2012_Group_C\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The winner will likely win the group.\", \"from\": 4259, \"to\": 4296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They will also face Puerto Rico and South Sudan in the group stage.\", \"from\": 4297, \"to\": 4364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4317, \"end\": 4328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.8778885992897709, \"rank\": 0.1390840278950955, \"text\": \"Puerto Rico\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puerto_Rico_national_baseball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hosts are capable of winning the gold medal.\", \"from\": 4366, \"to\": 4414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Victor Wembanyama will be appearing in his first Olympic tournament for France and alongside Minnesota Timberwolves center Rudy Gobert they may become the first Olympic team ever not to concede a field goal inside of 12 feet.\", \"from\": 4415, \"to\": 4640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4415, \"end\": 4432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\", \"score\": 0.9999841253316324, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Victor Wembanyama\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Victor_Wembanyama\"}, {\"begin\": 4487, \"end\": 4493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9901787418083507e-16, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4508, \"end\": 4517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Timberwolves\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.9431157152043405e-28, \"text\": \"Minnesota\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Timberwolves\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Timberwolves\"}, {\"begin\": 4518, \"end\": 4530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Timberwolves\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.618330166146232e-48, \"text\": \"Timberwolves\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Timberwolves\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota_Timberwolves\"}, {\"begin\": 4538, \"end\": 4549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudy_Gobert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rudy Gobert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudy_Gobert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rudy_Gobert\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fellow 2023 first-round pick Bilal Coulibaly will join Wemby as well as NBA veteran Nico Batum.\", \"from\": 4641, \"to\": 4736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4713, \"end\": 4716, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0288350946681754e-56, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 4725, \"end\": 4729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nico_Rosberg\", \"score\": 0.9999999096817233, \"rank\": 9.031807365860514e-08, \"text\": \"Nico\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nico_Rosberg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nico_Rosberg\"}, {\"begin\": 4730, \"end\": 4735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Batum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6531963325592606e-28, \"text\": \"Batum\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Batum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Batum\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As we have stated multiple times in our coverage, France's ability to get a gold medal will come down to their backcourt play.\", \"from\": 4738, \"to\": 4864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4788, \"end\": 4794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9901787418083507e-16, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"31 year old Evan Fournier and 38-year-old Nando De Colo are still their best point guards and pick-and-roll operators.\", \"from\": 4865, \"to\": 4983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4877, \"end\": 4890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Fournier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Evan Fournier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Fournier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Evan_Fournier\"}, {\"begin\": 4907, \"end\": 4920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nando_de_Colo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nando De Colo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nando_de_Colo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nando_de_Colo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will be tough to hide against Team USA or Canada for that matter.\", \"from\": 4984, \"to\": 5054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5019, \"end\": 5027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6445682992702308e-26, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5031, \"end\": 5037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.6643726021527911, \"rank\": 0.35105792818989034, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_men's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have got the length, skill, and defensive acumen to cover for them but it will not be easy and even then, can they still help create enough offense for France to compete with the best?\", \"from\": 5055, \"to\": 5244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5212, \"end\": 5218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9901787418083507e-16, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hosts will play their opening game on Saturday, July 27 against Brazil - an opponent they can not take lightly, Brazil is a feisty squad known for causing one upset in almost every tournament they play.\", \"from\": 5246, \"to\": 5452, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5314, \"end\": 5320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999985848262, \"rank\": 1.4151083093055808e-09, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5362, \"end\": 5368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999985848262, \"rank\": 1.4151083093055808e-09, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They will also face Germany and Japan in group play.\", \"from\": 5453, \"to\": 5505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5473, \"end\": 5480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.673947957810241e-13, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5485, \"end\": 5490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.6263151754411918, \"rank\": 0.4861130850565483, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Head coach Vincent Collet and his squad will certainly have their eyes set on the gold medal, but even winning a second consecutive silver medal would be a great feat given the competition in front of them.\", \"from\": 5506, \"to\": 5712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5517, \"end\": 5531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Collet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vincent Collet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Collet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vincent_Collet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's worth pointing out that Germany is the defending world champion, having beaten Serbia to capture the gold medal at the 2023 FIBA World Cup.\", \"from\": 5714, \"to\": 5858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5743, \"end\": 5750, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.673947957810241e-13, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5798, \"end\": 5804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9374100470996596, \"rank\": 0.06676902289838449, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sure, Team USA and Serbia did not have their best squads but you can only beat who's in front of you.\", \"from\": 5859, \"to\": 5960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5865, \"end\": 5873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6445682992702308e-26, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 5878, \"end\": 5884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9374100470996596, \"rank\": 0.06676902289838449, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's what Germany did, and the title of world champion is one they are currently wearing, and there is a chance they defend it.\", \"from\": 5961, \"to\": 6090, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5973, \"end\": 5980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.673947957810241e-13, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Germany is not loaded with elite NBA star power like some of the teams before them but they have got quality NBA starters and borderline stars, some role players, and a group of overseas professionals that fit together well to form a very balanced roster capable of beating anyone.\", \"from\": 6092, \"to\": 6373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6092, \"end\": 6099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.673947957810241e-13, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 6125, \"end\": 6128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0288350946681754e-56, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 6201, \"end\": 6204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0288350946681754e-56, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dennis Schroder and Franz Wagner take on the bulk of the scoring responsibility and Bayern Munich guard Andreas Obst provides the deadeye shooting gravity to open the floor up for them.\", \"from\": 6374, \"to\": 6559, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6374, \"end\": 6389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Schr\\u00f6der\", \"score\": 0.9999999485871753, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dennis Schroder\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Schr\\u00f6der\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dennis_Schr\\u00f6der\"}, {\"begin\": 6394, \"end\": 6406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Wagner_(basketball)\", \"score\": 0.9921778207483346, \"rank\": 0.00630666141111913, \"text\": \"Franz Wagner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Wagner_(basketball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franz_Wagner_(basketball)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Isaac Bonga, Oscar Da Silva, and Nick Weiler-Babb provide solid perimeter defense and their big-man rotations of Daniel Theis, Mo Wagner, Johannes Voigtmann, and Johannes Thiemann help control the backboards and clog the paint.\", \"from\": 6561, \"to\": 6788, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6561, \"end\": 6572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaac_Bonga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Isaac Bonga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaac_Bonga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isaac_Bonga\"